<Author>Adventurebuzz
<Content>Near perfection. My daughter and I stayed here for two nights in mid-May as our first stop on a two week tour of Spain. We booked a superior corner room with two balconies for $30 more per night. This is an NH hotel which has a superb reputation so the level of service and presentation was expected to be excellent. We weren't dissapointed in any respect. Staff was very attentive and friendly. Got us into the room at 11:00 so we could sleep off some jet lag. Rooms were not large, but fine, and the bath was adequate and newly remodeled modern. The big surprise was the location, which for us was the perfect spot in BCN. Right in the heart of the Gothic Quarter and a block from the shopping complex that winds its way through the quarter. Just far enough away from the Ramblas for no noise, an easy 3 block-5 minute walk from the airport bus that stops at Plaza Catalyuna (only way to go! and I hate busses). Five minutes from the Plaza Catalyuna metro stop. An easy downhill walk down the Ramblas to Montjuic (or metro to funicular). 5 minutes from the catherdral. Picasso Museo was ten minutes.Another nice surprise were the many pastry/bocadillo spots within a block or two. Easy to avoid the hotel's overpriced breakfasts.Only one drawback - wifi was pricey at 22 euros for 24 hours, or lobby computer for .35 euros a minute. Most hotels in Spain provide free wifi so this was definitely out of market for the country, but maybe not for Catalonia. 
