<Author>UKRoger
<Content>Great Hotel but a shame about the staff. The NH Duc de la Victoria could not be in a better location. Just 3 minutes walk away is the main centre of the city, Las Ramblas with its bars , restaurants and shops. The nearest metro link is about 5 minutes away, as is a tourist information centre.The hotel itself was spotless. The maids did an excellent job, cleaning the room each day and topping up the various freebies in the bathroom.I would have given this hotel a 5 point 'Excellent' rating if it had not been for the staff. 'Unhelpful' is an understatement.When we arrived in Barcelona, we took the Aerobus from the airport to the hotel. When we arrived in our room, my wife discovered that her purse was missing. We do not know if it was stolen or lost en route. Straight away I went down to the lobby and asked the staff for help. We had credit cards in the purse and some cash. We wanted to contact the airport and bus company to ask if it had been handed in. The response from the staff was shocking. They wouldn't telephone because they didn't know the number! (Couldn't be bothered to look it up). They didn't offer to help in any way and I felt as though they just wanted me to go away and stop disrupting their chat!We went to the tourist information office for help. It was packed with people, and yet the girls there were totally different. They looked up numbers, telephoned for us and did everything they could to help.The buffet breakfast was good with an large selection, mainly cold, but there was a server containing bacon, sausages and fried potatoes (chips). If you want eggs cooked (fried, boiled, etc) you just ask the waitress. But one morning we happened to sit on a table layed for three, (because it was in a nice spot) and we were told in a very rude and abrupt manner to move to a table for two. And that was after we had started to eat!Even as we left the hotel for our journey home, we asked the staff if they would be kind enough to check the flight information for us, but again...too much trouble.So, if you want to go to Barcelona, I certainly recommend the hotel. However, in case of an emergency, don't expect any help from the lobby staff...you're on your own there!. 
