<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Hotel for Exploring Barcelona !! Stayed at the hotel for 4 nights in July. On arrival at the airport, caught the A1 Aerobus from outside the terminal for a 40 mins journey to Placa De Catalunya. Price 3.60 euros each, and stops outside the department store El Cortes Ingles. Can be a bit of a scramble to board the bus with cases, bags, etc, but they come along so frequently its not a problem if the first couple are full. The hotel is just a 5-7 minute walk walk from the bus stop and is ideally situated for exploring Barcelona. It is set just off Les Rambles so as to be very quiet at night, yet close to everything that Barcelona has to offer. Good buffet breakfast with choice of tea/coffee, fruit juices, cereals, pastries, meat, cheese, etc. Didn't have much need to deal with reception staff but found them to be polite and efficient on arrival and upon checking out. Room was clean  tidy as was the bathroom. Towels changed daily  lots of bathroom toiletries. Tea  coffee making facility would have been nice and only one english speaking channel on the tv. Bought a two day pass for the bus turistic (17 euros each for 1 day, or 21 euros each for two days - must be conscecutive days). Children aged 4-12 charged 10 Euros  13 Euros respectively, under 4 are free. Once bought, you can get on  off the bus as many times as you like within the day, or two days. Its a great way to see everything that Barcelona has to offer. Two routes operate North (red) and South (blue) with a couple of transfer points from one route to the other along the way. The tour of barcelona Football club is a must for any football fan (red route) and you can get some great views of the city of Barcelona from the MNAC - Museu Nacional d'Art de Catalunya (blue route). You can buy tickets at the respective bus stops and although there may be lots of people queuing, its very well organised and the buses are very frequent. Its great to walk up  down Les Rambles - lots of human statues, artists, bird sellers, flower stalls, restaurants. Better still, visit the Attic restaurant for dinner (120 Les Rambles). Arrive early 6.45pm - 7.15pm and have a window seat overlooking Les Rambles and watch the world go by. If you prefer eating later would advise booking. Food is very good  extremely well presented, although don't expect it to be piled up on your plate. Cost approx 16 Euros per person for a main meal  dessert. If you like Italian, try Gino's which is situated at the port end of the Les Rambles, behind the shopping centre. If you want beefburgers there's always the Hard Rock Cafe on the Main Placa de Catalunya. Would definitely stay again !! 
